			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p><i>So it’s possible that bounties on enemy political leadership would be cheaper, more humane, and more effective than going to war. Why don’t governments use this tactic?</i></p>
<p>No mention of power vacuums? Many of these terrorist organisations (and here I include certain governments) are the incarnation of the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lernaean_Hydra" rel="nofollow">Hydra</a>. Cut off the head and two more spring out to attack you.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

